Octavio says, "The menu bar on the left-hand side allows visitors to navigate around the site."
A menu, "menu," bar, "bar," is a list of options or links on the website, usually to other pages on your website.
So, if you go to the ESL Pod website, you'll see links to other parts of our website: information about the podcast, how to subscribe using iTunes and so forth.
That list is called a menu bar, sometimes just simply a menu.
To navigate, "navigate," is the verb we use to mean to go to different places on the Internet or on a website.
You might say, "This website is very easy to navigate," meaning it's easy to find different parts of the website - to know where to go in the different parts of the website.
The verb to navigate has other meanings as well; take a look at the Learning Guide for additional definitions.
Margaret says to Octavio that she likes the layout of the website he's showing her.
Layout, "layout," is the same here as design.
